Create an HTML/JS/CSS website that does the following:

Take user input of start date daily budget amount

example: user enters the following:
StartDate	DailyBudget
12-29-2023	33

The website will show a calendar view of the following information:
Day	Date	CompoundBudget
Friday	12-29-2023	32
Saturday	12-30-2023	64
Sunday	12-31-2023	96
Monday	01-01-2024	128
Tuesday	01-02-2024	160
Wednesday	01-03-2024	192
Thursday	01-04-2024	224
Friday	01-05-2024	256
Saturday	01-06-2024	288
Sunday	01-07-2024	320
Monday	01-08-2024	352
Tuesday	01-09-2024	384
Wednesday	01-10-2024	416
Thursday	01-11-2024	448
Friday	01-12-2024	480

Calendar displays with the month in a typical calendar format of Sunday Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday Friday Saturday.
Example: first day of December 2023 was Friday Dec 1. It should be reflected as showing the first day as Friday, but also have a blank for the days that were not used like a typical calendar. Sunday Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday (Friday) Saturday

Based on user's budget start date and daily amount, start there. Any date before the date should have a blank amount, but still show the day.
First date starts with the daily budget amount, and then the next day gets the daily budget added again (compounding or accumulated).

have a section wher eusers can enter in expenses:
Item	Amount	Date
water	32	12-30-2023

the expense alters the calendar for 12-30-2023 to be:
Day	Date	CompoundBudget
Friday	12-29-2023	32
Saturday	12-30-2023	32
Sunday	12-31-2023	64
Monday	01-01-2024	96
Tuesday	01-02-2024	128
Wednesday	01-03-2024	160
Thursday	01-04-2024	192
Friday	01-05-2024	224
Saturday	01-06-2024	256
Sunday	01-07-2024	288
Monday	01-08-2024	320
Tuesday	01-09-2024	352
Wednesday	01-10-2024	384
Thursday	01-11-2024	416
Friday	01-12-2024	448

to reflect the expense on 12-30-2023

The user should be able to click on the date and a modal should appear displaying a header for date, then items for expense name, expense amount

The user should have the ability to go forward and backwards to see the various months to get an idea of how much money they can have.
As user moves from month to month, The days should continue to compound on each other and also continue to factor in expenses. 

Any days with expenses should show as a different color on the calendar so you can see upcoming expenses or days that were charged.

The user should be able to export the data into a csv so they can view it that way and have the ability to re-import the data.
